Cooper Ave. (corner thereon), west from the intersection of Cooper Ave. and 76th Street (richt foreground), showing in the foreground a brandspur of the Long Island Railroad. In the center of the view is une Glendale Hotel formerly the N. Wyckoff house located at the S.E.
corner of Cooper Ave. and 74th Street.
April 1923.
Eumene L. Armbruster Collection.
